        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Heteroscyphus knightii (Steph.) Grolle. 1. Sector of leading shoot, dorsal view. 2. Sector of leading shoot, ventral view. 3. Cladograph (U-shaped symbols = gynoecia). 4. Leaf pair and attached underleaf. 5-7. Leaves (all at same scale). 8. Leaf apices. 9. Portion of median lobe of 3-lobed leaf. 10. Median leaf cells. 11. Underleaf. (All from Engel 13121, Tasmania, Tasman Peninsula, near Taranna, near junction of Camp Road and Balt Spur Road.)" ;
